Barcelona Beats 10-Man Real Madrid 2-0 in Champions League Semifinal

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-04-27T20:57:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-27/barcelona-beats-10-man-real-madrid-2-0-in-champions-league-semifinal.html
Lionel Messi  scored both goals as
Barcelona defeated 10-man Real Madrid 2-0 in the opening game of
their Champions League soccer semifinal.  Messi scored in the 76th and 87th minutes at the Bernabeu
Stadium in Madrid. The FIFA World Player of the Year now has 52
goals for the season.  Real defender Pepe was sent off in the 61st minute, one of
three red and five yellow cards given out by referee Wolfgang
Stark. Real manager Jose Mourinho and Barcelona backup
goalkeeper Jose Pinto also received red cards.  It was the third meeting between the teams in 11 days. They
drew 1-1 in the Spanish league on April 16 before Real won 1-0
after extra time in the Copa del Rey final four days later.  Barcelona will host the return match in the two-game series
on May 3. The final of  Europe â€™s top club competition is May 28
at Wembley Stadium in  London .  Manchester yesterday won the first game in its semifinal 2-
0 at German club Schalke.  To contact the reporter on this story:
